WEBVTT

00:02.700 --> 00:04.368
This town meeting will come to order.

00:04.452 --> 00:07.704
- No one is listening to me.
- Taylor, calm down.

00:07.787 --> 00:09.872
I can't calm down. I'm being persecuted.

00:09.956 --> 00:13.333
- I promised that we'd hear you.
- We've been hearing you for 20 minutes.

00:13.376 --> 00:16.085
Excuse me, but some of us
have businesses to run...

00:16.169 --> 00:19.130
that don't involve
peddling drug paraphernalia to kids.

00:19.214 --> 00:20.673
It was a lava lamp, Taylor.

00:20.716 --> 00:23.550
There is no use for a lava lamp
unless you're on drugs.

00:23.635 --> 00:25.302
For crying out loud.

00:25.385 --> 00:28.972
Now, we've already agreed
to look into your accusation but to just...

00:29.055 --> 00:30.223
What'd I miss?

00:30.306 --> 00:33.767
Taylor Doose wants the no-parking zone
in front of his store removed.

00:33.851 --> 00:36.186
He says his customers
are being unfairly ticketed.

00:36.228 --> 00:39.231
- No, he just wants to park there all day.
- Genius.

00:39.314 --> 00:42.483
I have been mayor of this fine town
for a long time.

00:42.567 --> 00:45.486
I tend to think of all of you as my children.

00:45.569 --> 00:49.322
Unfortunately, sometimes children
have to be disciplined.

00:49.739 --> 00:53.534
Now, I'm gonna say something,
and I'm only gonna say it once.

00:54.118 --> 00:56.287
We have leash laws, people.

00:56.370 --> 00:57.538
Daddy's getting angry.

00:57.621 --> 01:00.832
- Rover will not leash himself.
- Good point.

01:01.332 --> 01:05.419
I would like to now move on
to something of even greater importance.

01:05.919 --> 01:08.463
As you all know, this coming Friday...

01:08.964 --> 01:12.801
is the anniversary of
the legendary Battle of Stars Hollow.

01:15.761 --> 01:17.387
- Where's Luke?
- There.

01:17.470 --> 01:20.014
Patty will be circulating a sign-up sheet...

01:20.098 --> 01:22.350
for those of you
who would like to participate...

01:22.433 --> 01:25.394
in the reenactment of the aforesaid battle.

01:25.602 --> 01:27.229
He's turning red.

01:27.521 --> 01:28.605
All right.

01:28.688 --> 01:33.192
"It was a frigid November night
some 224 years ago..."

01:33.276 --> 01:34.861
He's shifting in his seat.

01:34.944 --> 01:37.404
"...Hollow Militia
stood in wait for the redcoats."

01:37.445 --> 01:38.738
He's adjusting the cap.

01:38.780 --> 01:43.492
"Tired and hungry, 12 proud men
took their positions in the town square."

01:43.576 --> 01:45.411
He's fighting the urge.

01:45.453 --> 01:47.788
"...and imminent death
in their valiant efforts..."

01:47.871 --> 01:50.873
For God's sake, do we have to
go through this every damn year?

01:50.957 --> 01:52.917
- Yes!
- And the urge wins by a long shot.

01:52.958 --> 01:55.628
I thought we were here
to discuss town issues.

01:55.711 --> 01:57.213
This is a town issue.

01:57.296 --> 02:00.132
- Excuse me, who's talking?
- It's me, Harry. Luke.

02:00.215 --> 02:02.509
You've known me
since I was five years old.

02:02.592 --> 02:05.260
Luke, yes. Sit down.

02:05.803 --> 02:09.348
Now, as I was saying: "12 heroic men..."

02:09.764 --> 02:13.101
"assembled with guns drawn,
ready to meet their maker..."

02:13.184 --> 02:16.937
What are you talking about?
Twelve guys stood in a row all night.

02:16.979 --> 02:19.314
- "...waiting for the redcoats..."
- Who never showed!

02:19.397 --> 02:20.523
Now, just...

02:20.607 --> 02:23.943
Twelve guys stood in a row
waiting for an enemy that never showed.

02:23.984 --> 02:27.279
They got stood up. They should've
been wearing prom dresses.

02:27.529 --> 02:30.448
- I've had just about enough of this.
- Sit down, Taylor!

02:30.531 --> 02:31.783
- Menace.
- Suck up.

02:31.824 --> 02:33.951
- $5, someone ends up in a headlock.
- You're on.

02:33.992 --> 02:37.705
Have any of you considered the fact
that you're glorifying a war we fought...

02:37.788 --> 02:39.831
so we could keep land that we stole?

02:39.915 --> 02:41.917
If you don't like it here in America...

02:42.000 --> 02:46.712
why don't you go stand in line
for toilet paper in the USSR?

02:47.045 --> 02:49.464
There is no more USSR, Harry.

02:49.631 --> 02:52.800
A sense of community
is so important, isn't it?

02:53.051 --> 02:55.428
It's what made our country great.

02:55.511 --> 02:57.680
...if you're so interested in facts.

